adjectives.description: indigested (comparative more indigested, superlative most indigested)

entries.meaning: (now rare) Not resolved; not regularly disposed and arranged; unmethodical, crude.
examples: This, like an indigested meteor, appeared and disappeared almost at the same time.

entries.meaning: Not digested in the stomach; undigested.
(medicine, obsolete) Of wounds: not in a state suitable for healing; (specifically) of an abscess or its contents: not ripened or suppurated.
